@node inst "Installation of the pack"
@{u}How to install the whole thing properly...@{uu}

First, set the @{" palette " link "palette"}, then use an Icon utility like Iconian, SwazInfo (the best for that kind of job i think), etc... to replace your Icon Images by the BNS ones.
@endnode

@node cred "Thanks, Credits & Excuses"
@{b}CREDITS & THANKS@{ub}

First I would like to honorate my buddy S.B.Nose :

Thank you my brother, without you this hard work would have been nothing, long life and prosperty.  _\\V/

Then my NET-PAL Trevor MORRIS, who allowed me to use his icon template :

Thank you too, without your work, mine would have never existed. Hmm... Prolite's icons are a little antique for me Hmm... Err.

A special thank to MSD Informatique for having given me a 1438s monitor in exchange of mine (which has some problem). It helped me a lot for doing icons.

I don't (and I can't) forget :

Roman Patzner for his very-good RomIcons, Pix & patterns (Sorry for not having sent you a PostCard, but @{" Saint-Etienne " link "guide/SE/main"} is a horrible place to live in, if you win a travel to Saint-Etienne, offer it to your worst enemy, but I can
send you some postcard with an animal, baby, sexy or naked woman, famous-sites, food, etc...)

Martin Huttenloër XEN for creating Magic Workbench (Where's the "More than 8 colors" version of Magic Workbench ? Mmmmh ? Oh yeah. You're still enjoying from MWB2.0 registrations'big money in Acapulco ?)

H.-W.Schober for his Fast IPrefs (I got the version 40.35. I couldn''t close my WB screen with further versions of FastIPrefs)

R.E.Spence (the Guy behind RESICONS) I cut, remapped, reworked some of his icons to make mines, the part called @{" Set the 16 colors palette " link "palette"} is taken from his guide.

Makers of : Iconian (Chad Randall), PPaint (Cloanto), ADPro (I. Dunno).

@{b}EXCUSES@{ub}

Yes ! I also make mistakes, the proof...

Mommy, I'm sorry for all bad things I've made to you :

During nine months, she held me deep inside her, loved me, took care of me when I was ill, cried for me when I was away, grew me the man I am today.

@{i}I dedicate this work to all the mothers around the world and especially the broken mothers of Algeria. @{ui}

Daddy, I'm sorry for all bad things I've made to you

During a long time, he worked hard to get for mum & me the necessary, took care of us, loved us, taught me the good and the bad

The readers, I'm sorry for my distorted English.
@endnode

